# GIN Lipid Embeddings

Pretrained GIN embeddings for all 14 lipids in the LANCE dataset.

## Files
- `gin_inference.py` — generates embeddings from SMILES
- `model.py` — GIN architecture (adapted from snap-stanford/pretrain-gnns)
- `supervised_contextpred.pth` — pretrained weights (chem, context prediction)
- `lance_lipid_gin_embeddings.npy` — output embeddings
- `sanity_check.py` — validates embeddings (shape, NaN, zeros)
- `similarity_matrix.py` — pairwise cosine similarity matrix + plot

## Embeddings Format
Dictionary saved as .npy file. Keys are SMILES strings, values are 300-dim numpy arrays.

To load:

    embeddings = np.load('lance_lipid_gin_embeddings.npy', allow_pickle=True).item()
    emb = embeddings["SMILES_STRING"]  # returns np.array of shape (300,)

## Model Details
- Architecture: GIN (Graph Isomorphism Network), 5 layers, emb_dim=300, JK=last
- Pretraining: Supervised + context prediction on chemistry dataset (ZINC/ChEMBL)
- Weights source: snap-stanford/pretrain-gnns (chem/model_gin/supervised_contextpred.pth)
- Pooling: Global mean pooling over node representations

## Key Finding
Cholesterol and beta-sitosterol produce nearly identical embeddings (cosine sim=0.9946) despite having different efficacy profiles in the LANCE dataset. This motivates the use of richer 3D-aware encoders (SchNet, 3D Infomax) as explored in the broader project.

